</p>
<figcaption>You can watch the Stuntman Hollywood announcement trailer here.<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7NZpeAmdxk" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>


<p>The game seems focused on exciting action and chaotic movie moments, as the announcement trailer shows driving and a few chaotic crashes stunts all over the place. Much of which is elaborated on in <a href="https://blog.playstation.com/2026/06/02/stuntman-hollywood-announced-coming-soon-to-ps5/">an official PlayStation blog</a> released alongside the trailer.
</p><p>In this blog, genre influences including Burnout and Split/Second are mentioned explicitly. The post reads: "The entire game is built around movie shoots, where you perform stunts in all kinds of vehicles including legends like the Time Machine and KITT along with many other cars, SUVs, motorcycles, and even a school bus."
</p>
<p>The post explains that each mission will have a director set certain goals for the player to complete, such as drifting through a section or riding on two wheels. You'll also be able to collect a number of rewards for your personal garage, which will highlight your most exciting moments.
</p>
<p>I, for one, cannot believe I've seen Death Race representation in 2026.
</p>
<p>The game is wishlistable now, and while there's no release date announced as of writing, the game is coming to the PS5. Hopefully soon!</p>

